# MCP Integration

## Server

- Name: `__MCP_SERVER_NAME__`
- Transport: `__MCP_TRANSPORT__`
- Command: `__MCP_COMMAND__`
- Auth profile: `__MCP_AUTH_PROFILE__`
- Token source: `__MCP_TOKEN_SOURCE__`

## Generated Files

- `.cursor/mcp.json.example` is always generated.
- `.cursor/mcp.json` is only generated when the launcher is run with
  `--with-mcp-config`. It is gitignored to avoid leaking auth-bearing
  configuration.

## Tools

Project: `project_register`, `project_get`, `project_list`, `project_update`,
`project_health_check`, `project_archive`.

Backlog: `backlog_import`, `backlog_sync` with `mode = validate_only|import|sync`
and `conflict_policy = fail|warn|overwrite_mcp|overwrite_local`.

Tasks: `task_create`, `task_plan`, `task_assign`, `task_claim_next`,
`task_status`, `task_list`, `task_cancel`, `task_review`, `task_approve`,
`task_reject`, `task_get_artifacts`, `task_get_evidence`, `task_get_audit_log`.

## Resources

`aitask://projects`, `aitask://projects/{id}`, `/backlog`, `/tasks`,
`/schedules`, `/evidence`, `/quality-dashboard`, `/improvement-reports`.

## OKF Context

OKF is the local source-of-context for project knowledge. The lifecycle MCP should treat `.okf` as reviewable project context and preserve task links declared through `okf_concepts`.

## Delivery Boundary

- This project ships MCP wrapper scripts and contracts.
- Full MCP foundation hardening (authn/authz enforcement, strict project isolation,
  durable audit/event persistence, and transport convergence) is an external server
  dependency and must be completed in the MCP server codebase before default
  non-readonly automation is enabled.
